# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: 1879-providence-grays-season
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:1879-providence-grays-season/1876-chicago-white-stockings-season] The **1876 Chicago White Stockings season** was the fifth season of the Chicago White Stockings franchise, the first in the National League and the third at 23rd Street Grounds.
[src:1879-providence-grays-season/1876-chicago-white-stockings-season] The White Stockings, as one of the founding members of the new National League, won the NL's initial championship during this season with a record of 52–14.
[src:1879-providence-grays-season/1877-boston-red-caps-season] The **1877 Boston Red Caps season** was the seventh season of the franchise.
[src:1879-providence-grays-season/1877-boston-red-caps-season] Arthur Soden became the new owner of the franchise, who won their first National League pennant.
[src:1879-providence-grays-season/1878-boston-red-caps-season] The **1878 Boston Red Caps season** was the eighth season of the franchise.
[src:1879-providence-grays-season/1878-boston-red-caps-season] The Red Caps won their second straight National League pennant.
[src:1879-providence-grays-season/1878-providence-grays-season] The **Providence Grays** were a new franchise that joined the National League for the 1878 baseball season.
[src:1879-providence-grays-season/1879-boston-red-caps-season] The **1879 Boston Red Caps season** was the ninth season of the franchise.
[src:1879-providence-grays-season/1879-buffalo-bisons-season] The 1879 season was the debut year in the National League for the **Buffalo Bisons**, who had previously played an independent schedule.
[src:1879-providence-grays-season/1879-buffalo-bisons-season] The Bisons wound up with a record of 46–32 and finished in third place.
[src:1879-providence-grays-season/1879-chicago-white-stockings-season] The **1879 Chicago White Stockings season** was the eighth season of the Chicago White Stockings franchise, the fourth in the National League and the second at Lakefront Park.
[src:1879-providence-grays-season/1879-chicago-white-stockings-season] The White Stockings finished fourth in the National League with a record of 46–33.
[src:1879-providence-grays-season/1879-providence-grays-season] The **1879 Providence Grays** won the National League title in only their second season in the league.
